$ R probability distribution functions: prefix

Most (all?) R probability functions come with four prefixes: `r`, `p`, `d`, `q`.

{ r - random deviates

  gh|about-r|/functions/_probability-distribution/_prefix/r.R||

  gh|about-r|/functions/_probability-distribution/_prefix/img/r.png||

}
{ d - density 

  The `d` prefix stands for the *probability density function* (PDF).

  The PDF is added onto the plot, showing that the shape of the histogram tends to converge to the shape of the PDF as the number of random
  variables increases.

  gh|about-r|/functions/_probability-distribution/_prefix/d.R||

  gh|about-r|/functions/_probability-distribution/_prefix/img/d.png||

}
